all of these white-power freaks need to do us all a favor and put bullets in their own heads. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unosfy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nosfy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 256<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/18/01 7:45:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Words of an Afghani living in the US</span><hr size=1> Massoud who was the leader of the resistance against Talibans is dead Saturday. It is a hard blow to the resistance. Massoud was one of those people who believe in peace and in freedom in his country. Having read some of his interviews, I can say that thios man didnt deserved to die like this.<br>
