Marr</b><BR><i>I am going, I am going<BR>Any which way the wind may blowing<BR>I am going, I am going<BR>Where streams of whiskey are flowing</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uealan01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ealan01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/18/01 9:50:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Words of an Afghani living in the US</span><hr size=1> A massive ground war against Afghanistan is unwinable and will only serve to kill millions of innocents; in addition, it may very well destabilize Pakistan.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the Taliban is in the comfortable position that extremist regimes always wind up in.  They literally have a human shield of innocents that they can utilize to protect them while they consume 100% of the nations resources.<br>
<br>
It was truly sad to see the legions of Afghanis trying to leave the country; a battered people who have suffered far more than any people ever should.<br>
<br>
I don't really know what an acceptable course of action is in a case like this.  Afghanistan is unique in that it is very nearly unasailable.  It is controlled by a radical government that will not negotiate and has been incorrectly empowered by a major nation (I think Pakistan never realized how bad the Taliban would become).<br>
<br>
I do not think, however, that we will see an enormous land blitzkrieg or a continuous program of bombing.  Those actions would simply accomplish nothing other than killing innocents and, despite the rhetoric of our enemies, modern America does not revel in the loss of innocent lives.<br>
<br>
